<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,151,1257]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,979,1005]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Zahniser)" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zahniser" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[323,738,979,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasileira">
<emphasis box="[323,613,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Paraclorindaia brasileira</emphasis>
(Zahniser)
</taxonomicName>
is removed from 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1062,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[939,1062,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here based on the refined definition of 
<taxonomicName box="[237,360,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[237,360,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the description of the new genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[803,976,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[803,976,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Paraclorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zahniser" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[992,1132,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasileira">
<emphasis box="[992,1132,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. brasileira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the ocelli close to the anterior margin of the head, anterior margin of the head not carinate, male pygofer with several macrosetae, and male pygofer with posteroventral claw, which justifies removal from 
<taxonomicName box="[928,1051,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[928,1051,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and placement in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[1257,1430,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1430,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Paraclorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two genera share the texture of the frontoclypeus which is mostly smooth and shiny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,151,1257]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName box="[199,322,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,322,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(three members included in the phylogenetic analysis here) was resolved as monophyletic, but its relationship to other genera of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[533,615,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Faltala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
